# Azan Notification Style & Custom Audio

We will update the application to support fully customized Azan notification styles, including bundled Adhan MP3s.

## Open Questions

None at this moment. We will use standard open-source Mecca Adhan audio.

## Proposed Changes

### Assets / Audio Files
- We will download two standard MP3s and place them in `app/src/main/res/raw/`:
  - `full_adhan.mp3`: The full Adhan sound.
  - `first_adhan.mp3`: Just the opening Takbeer ("Allahu Akbar").

### Settings & Translation
- **Update Settings Label**: Rename "Sound type" to "Azan Notification style" in the UI.
- **Update Options**: Change the underlying options to:
  1. `Full Azan Sound`
  2. `The First of Azan (الله اكبر)`
  3. `Default notification sound`
  4. `Vibration only`
- Add proper translation keys in `Translation.kt` for both English and Arabic.

### [MODIFY] `SettingsScreen.kt`
- Update the dialog that controls the notification sound setting to use the new string keys.
- Change the display logic to format the options properly.

### [MODIFY] `PrayerNotificationReceiver.kt`
- **Notification Channels**: Android requires a new unique Channel ID if the sound changes. We will map the 4 options to 4 distinct channel IDs (`prayer_channel_full`, `prayer_channel_first`, `prayer_channel_default`, `prayer_channel_vibrate`).
- **Audio Configuration**: Load the custom `Uri` from `R.raw.full_adhan` and `R.raw.first_adhan` and apply it to the respective channels using `setSound()`.
- Add explicit vibration patterns for "Vibration only".

### [MODIFY] `SettingsViewModel.kt` & `Entities.kt` (if required)
- Ensure the initial/default value handles the new string identifiers smoothly.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `.\gradlew.bat compileDebugKotlin` to ensure no syntax errors.

### Manual Verification
- Review the Settings Screen UI to confirm the label is "Azan Notification style" and all 4 options are visible and selectable.
- Confirm the MP3 files are successfully downloaded and packaged into the APK.
